
% git clone git+ssh://kkyi@scm.gforge.inria.fr/gitroot/itsa/itsa.git
will make a cloned checkout in this directory, generating itsa
directory.

When doing with others, always do (pull;edit;pull;commit;push)
% git pull
% (* edit locals *)
% git pull (in case update may be done by other sides)
% git commit -a -m "message"
% git push

----
% git pull
copies new version to local repository

If 'git pull' generates a conflict
% git stash  (* stash local copy *)
% git pull   (* bring in new version from repositary *)
% git stash apply (* merge the stashed to the new version *)
Or,
% git stash pop (* merge the stashed to the new version & remove the stashed *)

If 'git pull' generated a conflict and you want to forget about the stashed 
% git stash  (* stash local copy *)
% git pull   (* bring in new version from repository *)
% git stash drop (* delete the stashed/forget about the stashed *)

After editing files, 
% git commit -a -m "message"
% git push
will update the remote repositary

If 'git push' generates a conflict
% git stash
% git pull
% git pop

When you want to try a branch
% git branch foo (* consider a branch named "foo" *)
% git checkout foo (* default becomes the foo branch *)
% (* edit locals, i.e.,  edit the foo branch *)
% git commit -a -m "message" (* foo is commited as a branch *)

If you are happy with the branch and want to merge it into the main trunk
% git checkout master (* default becomes the main trunk *)
% (* edit locals, i.e., edit the master branch, in case you work on the main *)
% git merge foo (* merge foo branch to the main trunk *)

---

To add a new file foo.tex, do
% git add foo.tex
% git commit -m "message"
% git push

---

When github asks login/passwd, login = kwangkeun passwd = use access token.
To get the access token:
visit github.com;
click my photo;
visit settings;
visit Developer settings;
visit Personal access tokens;
click Generate new token;
enter any char into Note box;
set expiration No expiration;
click repo box;
click Generate token;
copy the generated token and use it as password.
